18:06.740 --> 18:08.400
And here are your hosts.

18:13.060 --> 18:17.340
This is Daryl Ayn and David Carson. The Science Fiction of Dean Ayn is always exciting and fast

18:17.340 --> 18:22.720
paced, making it difficult for readers to put his books down. But his work also has messages to it,

18:22.900 --> 18:26.880
some information, some opinions that Ayn wishes to communicate through the entertaining and exciting

18:26.880 --> 18:31.940
narrative. Anasazi, systemic shock, and soft targets are all good examples of exciting science

18:31.940 --> 18:36.740
fiction novels by Ayn which carry some messages or information along with the story. Ayn bases his

18:36.740 --> 18:40.940
writing on ideas which he's interested in at the time he writes. He tells us about some of his

18:40.940 --> 18:46.180
interests. There are a couple of themes that have occupied me a lot.

18:48.640 --> 18:57.040
One of them other people have begun to come up to, begun to work on such that I can move on to

18:57.040 --> 19:04.320
something else again, I would say that sensible transportation, mass transit, cars that get

19:04.320 --> 19:09.120
50 to 100 miles a gallon, things like that, things that I was demonstrating working on,

19:09.120 --> 19:15.860
building cars that got 50 miles a gallon 20 years ago when nobody else cared. Now a lot of people care

19:16.560 --> 19:21.860
and now I'm not interested in it much anymore because it's already been, not because of me

19:21.860 --> 19:29.760
really, but for whatever reason it has been taken up as an important issue. The second thing

19:30.560 --> 19:37.600
along that line would be survival. Not only nuclear survival but various other kinds. I write in

19:37.600 --> 19:47.700
survival publications. I design backpackers wood stoves and all kinds of other gadgetry

19:48.920 --> 19:56.400
that would be very useful in survival contexts. I've had to make my own snowshoes to get out of

19:56.400 --> 20:04.420
the high Sierra on one particular summer, which was hardly like a summer at all. It was a very

20:04.420 --> 20:14.240
late spring, but survival in particular in the nuclear holocaust survival issue is one that I

20:14.240 --> 20:16.900
have dealt with for two or three years now.

20:26.060 --> 20:29.860
Inge's latest book is a good example of his method of writing about his immediate concerns.

20:29.860 --> 20:32.660
It's called Pulling Through and it's based on the theme of survival.

21:03.400 --> 21:08.180
Inge says he normally tries to proportion his stories between 90% entertainment and 10%

21:08.180 --> 21:11.320
information, but pulling through is a slight departure from that formula.

21:29.860 --> 21:38.480
In the context of a great big overbearing and overwhelming bounty hunter in California,

21:39.120 --> 21:46.060
the kind of guy who goes around with weapons all the time and has a fairly high tech environment,

21:46.440 --> 21:51.060
he's a man around whom things just happen and they happen fast.

22:12.260 --> 22:16.740
Pulling Through is definitely not a dull novel. It's a fresh experiment in science fiction and one that will

22:16.740 --> 22:20.900
fascinate readers. We hope Inge continues to include information in his books along with the

22:20.900 --> 22:23.580
narrative. That's really what science fiction is all about anyhow.

